title: Production of Chickens , turkeys , chicks , poults in Canada 2017
summary: The Production of Chickens turkeys in Canada during 2017 has been increasing over the year .
Even that , several fluctuations have been recorded , in particular during the first months of the year .
The maximum values have been recorded during November and December .
gold: Production of poultry including chickens , turkeys , chicks and poults reaches its maximum during the month of May with a number of 1215 in Canada . The biggest increase in production of poultry can be observed from February until May , while a drop from May to July takes place . From August until November the production remains quite stable at approximately 1205 and starts decreasing until it reaches its minimum in February below 1190 .
